title: For Trade:  SOLD! - New AR-15 .223 Wylde SPR chambered for 5.56 Nato / .223
postcontent:
SOLD! 
 
I have a new and upgraded AR-15 SPR chambered for 5.56 / .223 with .223 Wylde Barrel that I would like to sell or trade. This rifle is new and has not taken to the range nor fired. Round count on rifle is zero.
Parts:-  Matched PSA Upper and Lower with Palmetto Start Armory (PSA) Logo Rollmarks on both receivers.  (This is a premium build rifle and not an entry level budget 'Daily Deal'.)-  Barrel upgraded to an accurate premium grade 16" barrel chambered in .223 Wylde with A2 Birdcage Flash Hider-  Mil-spec Carpenter 158 steel, Shot peened, High pressure tested and Mag Particle Inspected Full Auto Capable Bolt Carrier Group-  Magpul SL-K Stock - Mil Spec (in Black)-  Magpul MOE carbine Handguard (in Black)-  Yankee Hill Machine YHM-9395 Folding Front Sight / Gas Block-  Ambidextrous Safety Selector-  Ambidextrous AR-15 Rear Sling Mount Adapter Loop- (2)x Mags- Rifle Case
Not familiar with the .223 Wylde barrel chambering? 
The .223 Wylde is a hybrid .223/5.56 chamber designed by Bill Wylde to yield the accuracy advantages of the match .223 Remington commercial chambering, but without pressure or reliability failures when using high velocity 5.56 NATO spec ammunition.  The .223 Wylde achieves better accuracy by having a chamber throat that is tighter than 5.56, but will still function reliably with military 5.56 ammunition because the case dimensions are the same. These facts lead to the .223 Wylde having superior target and varmint accuracy, a compatibility with all .223 and 5.56 NATO ammunitions, and being a top choice for competition shooters.
Is there a compelling reason to switch to a Wylde chamber? Well, the most obvious reason is that you can fire .223 ammo without giving up accuracy and 5.56 ammo without worrying about excess pressure. Sure, you can fire .223 ammo all day from a 5.56 without worrying about pressure problems thanks to generous chamber size, but if you really want to tighten those groups that .2240 freebore diameter helps. In fact, .223 Wylde chambers are known for extreme accuracy, which is better on the whole than what you can expect from a standard 5.56×45 chamber.Buyer / Trade Partner Requirement: Anyone I conduct a transaction with must have valid Florida Driver's license / ID.  I will not sell to anyone under 21. I prefer working individuals that are CWP holders.  Individuals I work with must be willing to fillout paperwork and sign a bill of sale. I vet everyone I sell to or trade with so do not contact me if you are a felon.  I will check criminal history and if you have a record it will come out so do not bother trying to lie your way through a transaction. I guarantee trying to circumvent any of these requirements will cause the transaction to fail and ultimately waste everyone's time. If you are looking for a backroom undocumented or non-registered sale you will want to find someone else to work with.
